Historical overview of the existence of German population in the Baltics, typical features of Baltic-German language, lexicography, Baltic-German, Estonian and Latvian common cultural field and its manifestation in language, literature and biographical writing.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction into historical Baltic-German culture, language and literature as an organic part of Estonian culture and one of possible regional objectives of German Studies in Estonia through reading and translating of different literary, biographical, scientific and esseistic texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course, students will have insight in Baltic-German culture, language and literature and will have basic knowledge of  understanding and translating of Baltic-German texts.
